<li id="cite_note-7"><b><a href="#cite_ref-7" title="">^</a></b> Since the identity of Alois' biological father is an unsolved mystery of Third Reich history, it is consequently impossible to determine the true biological relationship between Alois and Klara. <i>See</i> discussion in <a href="/wiki/Alois_Hitler" title="Alois Hitler">Alois Hitler</a> article. If, as the official records (as modified when Alois was 39 years old) show, <a href="/wiki/Johann_Georg_Hiedler" title="Johann Georg Hiedler">Johann Georg Hiedler</a> was Alois' biological father, then Alois and Klara were first cousins, once removed; if <a href="/wiki/Johann_Nepomuk_Hiedler" title="Johann Nepomuk Hiedler">Johann Nepomuk Hiedler</a> (the younger brother of Johann Georg) was his biological father, then Alois was Klara's half-uncle. In either case Alois and Klara were within the proscribed degrees of <a href="/wiki/Consanguinity" title="Consanguinity">consanguinity</a>.</li>
